<br>
<br></span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-877e066e"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-4035877e">In recent years, many national governments have begun investing in the cacao industry, either in local farmers (as in the Philippines) or in those of a nearby country (as in New Zealand’s involvement in Timor-Leste). With the explosion of the <a href="https://barandcocoa.com/pages/what-is-craft-chocolate" style="font-weight: bold;" target="_self">craft chocolate movement</a>, some farmers are now growing cacao aimed at a high-end market. In some countries which grow cacao, there’s only one producer buying up cacao from local farmers or growing it on a single plantation.
